  "body": "**Description**\r\n\r\nSince removing the OVM, we no longer use the `update()` functionality in `Lib_SecureMerkleTrie` (for reference the call [occurred here](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/86a13dcb0cfc2050317797d031917a2585ce2a49/packages/contracts/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/OVM/verification/OVM_StateTransitioner.sol#L439)). \r\n\r\nWe shouldn't have unused code lying around, so we should remove `Lib_SecureMerkleTrie.update()`, and any code which was used only by it.\r\n\r\n**ToDo**\r\n\r\n1. Delete [the `update()` function](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/3dee2651d720f492eb4b5d7fcebf2cd29f485afc/packages/contracts/contracts/libraries/trie/Lib_SecureMerkleTrie.sol#L48) in the secure trie lib.\r\n\r\n2. Delete [the `update()` function](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/3dee2651d720f492eb4b5d7fcebf2cd29f485afc/packages/contracts/contracts/libraries/trie/Lib_MerkleTrie.sol#L92) in the regular trie lib. \r\n\r\n3. Delete any other `internal` helper functions which were only used in `update()` and so are no longer used. (Keep deleting code until the compiler complains about it).\r\n\r\n4. Delete any tests that tested the deleted code.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
